# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if development environment varies, Pipfile.lock may cause conflict.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   Reference: https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; dependency directory created by pipflow via `pdm install --pep582`
__pypackages__/

